<item>
            <title>[LU-19173] inode_attach_wb() / __inode_attach_wb() symbol has been removed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19173</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;inode_attach_wb() was made a wrapper for __inode_attach_wb() and made generally available:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v5.2-2705-g9b0eb69b75bc&lt;br/&gt;
  cgroup, blkcg: Prepare some symbols for module and !CONFIG_CGROUP&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.12-rc1-25-g8182a8b39aa2&lt;br/&gt;
   writeback: wbc_attach_fdatawrite_inode out of line&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;__inode_attach_wb() symbol is not exported making inode_attach_wb() unavailable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Defer the check on attached wb inode until inode has wb attached (inode is marked dirty).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
